			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Contaminated sites are areas where the environment has been adversely affected by hazardous substances. These sites can be managed at national, state, or local levels, with oversight from entities like the EPA and its partners. The presence of contamination can be concerning due to potential health and environmental hazards. While some sites may pose little risk, others can have significant impacts depending on the contamination type, concentration, and exposure mechanisms. </common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">受污染场所是指环境受到有害物质不利影响的区域。这些场所可以在国家、州或地方各级进行管理，并由环保局及其合作伙伴等实体进行监督。由于潜在的健康和环境危害，污染的存在可能令人担忧。虽然一些地点可能风险很小，但其他地点可能会产生重大影响，这取决于污染类型、浓度和暴露机制。</common:generalComment>
